South Africa has recorded 772 new coronavirus cases, bringing the total number of cases to 727 595.  In a statement, the Department of Health also reported 54 COVID-19 related deaths. “Twenty-four from Eastern Cape, 13 from the Free State, one from KwaZulu-Natal, two from Limpopo, one from Mpumalanga, nine from Northern Cape, and four from Western Cape. ” This brings the total number of COVID-19 related deaths to 19 465. “Of the 54 deaths reported today, four were reported to have occurred in the past 24-48 hours: one in KwaZulu-Natal, and three in Western Cape.” The recoveries now stand at 657 500 which translates to a recovery rate of 90%. Below are the latest COVID-19 stats in South Africa: 4 852 918 727 595 657 500 50 630 19 465 676 965 As at 02 November 2020 10 402 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));